  "prompt": "What oozes out of a bug bite?",
  "response": "When a bug bite becomes infected or irritated, several substances might ooze out:\n\n1. Clear fluid/serum\n- Typically a clear, watery liquid\n- Part of the body's natural healing response\n- Contains proteins and antibodies\n\n2. Pus\n- Yellowish or greenish fluid\n- Contains dead white blood cells\n- Indicates possible bacterial infection\n\n3. Blood\n- May occur if the bite is scratched or damaged\n- Small amount of blood can seep out\n\n4. Plasma\n- Yellowish, sticky liquid\n- Similar to clear fluid but slightly thicker\n\nThe specific discharge depends on the type of bug bite, your body's reaction, and whether the bite has become infected. If you're experiencing significant discharge, redness, swelling, or pain, it's best to consult a healthcare professional.",
